 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Item&nbsp;7.01. Regulation FD Disclosure. </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On February&nbsp;17, 2015, we issued a press release relating to the presentation made by Mondel&#275;z International executives at the 2015 Consumer Analyst
Group of New York conference. A copy of the press release is being furnished as Exhibit 99.1 to this Current Report on Form 8-K. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A live audio webcast of
the presentation will be available through the Investor Center section of our website, <U>www.mondelezinternational.com</U>. An archived rebroadcast and the presentation slides will also be available through our website following the webcast. The
presentation slides, including Regulation G reconciliations, are being furnished as Exhibit 99.2 to this Current Report on Form 8-K. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">This information,
including Exhibits 99.1 and 99.2, will not be deemed &#147;filed&#148; for purposes of Section&nbsp;18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#147;Exchange Act&#148;), or otherwise subject to the liabilities under that section and
it will not be incorporated by reference in any filing under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, or the Exchange Act, except as expressly set forth by specific reference in such a filing. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="right"><B>Exhibit 99.1 </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g873683g22j13.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><U>news@mdlz.com</U></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Mondel&#275;z International Reiterates Strategy and Details Progress on Margin-Improvement Plans at CAGNY
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">BOCA RATON, Fla. &#150; Feb. 17, 2015 &#150; At the Consumer Analyst Group of New York (CAGNY) conference today, executives of
Mondel&#275;z International reinforced the company&#146;s long-term growth strategy and highlighted progress to expand margins through its supply chain reinvention and overhead cost-reduction initiatives. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;In the current challenging environment, we&#146;re executing against our transformation agenda by controlling what we can control,
reducing costs, pricing to protect profitability and driving our Power Brands and innovation platforms in key markets,&#148; said Irene Rosenfeld, Chairman and CEO. &#147;By executing these strategies, we&#146;re well-positioned to continue to
deliver strong shareholder value through sustainable, profitable growth over the long term.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Long-Term Strategy to Deliver Sustainable Profitable
Growth </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Rosenfeld reiterated the company&#146;s long-term targets of Organic Net Revenue growth at or above category growth rates,
high-single digit Adjusted Operating Income growth at constant currency and double-digit Adjusted EPS growth at constant currency. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;In 2015, however, we&#146;ll continue to prioritize margin expansion and earnings growth while delivering modest organic revenue growth,
as we progress our transformation agenda to focus our portfolio on snacks, reduce costs and invest for long-term growth,&#148; Rosenfeld said. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">With respect to portfolio focus, the company is expected to close its coffee joint venture with D.E Master Blenders 1753 later this year and
will add two acquisitions in snacking, Kinh Doh in Vietnam and U.S.-based Enjoy Life Foods. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Rosenfeld also shared examples of how the
company continues to invest for growth by increasing support behind its Power Brands, innovation platforms and routes to market. In 2014, Power Brands represented more than 60 percent of net revenue and received about 80 percent of the
company&#146;s A&amp;C investment. And through successful innovation platforms such as <I>belVita</I> biscuits, <I>Bubbly</I> and <I>Marvellous Creations</I> chocolate, the company has quickly expanded products across multiple geographies to
accelerate growth. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">1 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Supply Chain Reinvention on Track to Achieve Margin Goals </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Daniel Myers, Executive Vice President, Integrated Supply Chain, provided an update on the company&#146;s journey to reinvent its supply chain,
which is on track to deliver $3 billion in gross productivity savings, $1.5 billion in net productivity and $1 billion in incremental cash flow over three years. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Myers highlighted how the company is transforming its manufacturing processes to develop more efficient, modular designs for global product
platforms, called &#147;Lines of the Future.&#148; These advantaged lines are cutting conversion costs by 30 percent in biscuits and 20 percent in chocolate and in gum as they replace older, more inefficient assets. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;Our Lines of the Future are driving significant savings in reduced engineering, installation and start-up costs. And we&#146;re reducing
conversion costs through increased throughput, less waste and lower staffing per line,&#148; said Myers. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">At the same time, Mondel&#275;z
International is restructuring its end-to-end supply chain network. From 2013 to 2015, the company will have funded and built 11 new or expanded manufacturing plants around the world, including in Bahrain, Brazil, China and India. By 2018, the
company expects to build another five sites. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;When we started our journey, only 15 percent of our Power Brands were produced on
advantaged assets,&#148; said Myers. &#147;By 2018, we expect that number to be about 70 percent.&#148; Myers said the goal is to have all of the company&#146;s Power Brands produced on advantaged assets in advantaged locations at advantaged costs.
Revenue per plant is expected to increase more than 50 percent from $200 million per plant in 2012 to more than $300 million by 2018. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Finally, Myers emphasized the team&#146;s significant cash flow progress. Since 2012, the company has reduced its cash conversion cycle by 23
days, resulting in $600 million in incremental cash last year. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Targeting Overhead Reduction through Best-in-Class Cost Management </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;Overhead savings will also be a major contributor to margin gains,&#148; said Brian Gladden, Executive Vice President and CFO.
&#147;Using a zero-based-budgeting approach, we significantly reduced overhead as a percentage of revenue in 2014. This puts us well on our way to reduce overheads by at least 200 basis points by 2016.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As a result of cost reduction progress in both the supply chain and overheads, Adjusted Operating Income<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP> margin increased by 80 basis points to 12.9 percent in 2014, despite absorbing a 50-basis-point headwind from mark-to-market accounting. </P>
<P STYLE="line-height:8.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:10%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Adjusted Operating Income is a non-GAAP financial measure. Please see discussion of non-GAAP financial measures at the end of this press release for more information. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">2 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Affirmed 2015 Outlook </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The company affirmed its 2015 outlook: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Organic Net Revenue growth of at least 2 percent, after accounting for the company&#146;s strategic decision to exit certain lower-margin revenue </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Adjusted Operating Income margin of approximately 14 percent </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

flow. The company delivered Free Cash Flow excluding items<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP> of $4.8 billion over the past two years, up nearly 30 percent versus the company&#146;s earlier guidance, primarily driven by margin
expansion and the strong improvement in working capital. In 2015, the company expects to deliver Free Cash Flow of at least $1.2 billion, excluding the impact of the expected coffee transaction. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Reinvesting in the business to drive growth will remain the top priority for cash. The company will also continue to explore opportunities for
acquisitions to strengthen capabilities in its snacks categories. Finally, the company expects to continue to return capital to shareholders in the form of share buybacks and dividends while maintaining an investment grade credit rating. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">A live audio webcast of the CAGNY presentation will be available in the investors section of the company&#146;s website
(<U>www.mondelezinternational.com</U>) at 12:30 p.m. ET today. An archived replay of the presentation with accompanying slides will be available on the website following the webcast. The company will be live tweeting from the event at
<U>www.twitter.com/MDLZ</U>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>About Mondel&#275;z International </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. (NASDAQ: MDLZ) is a global snacking powerhouse, with 2014 revenue of $34 billion. Creating delicious moments
of joy in 165 countries, Mondel&#275;z International is a world leader in biscuits, chocolate, gum, candy, coffee and powdered beverages, with billion-dollar brands such as <I>Oreo, LU</I> and <I>Nabisco</I> biscuits;<I> Cadbury, Cadbury Dairy Milk
</I>and <I>Milka</I> chocolate; <I>Trident</I> gum; <I>Jacobs</I> coffee and <I>Tang</I> powdered beverages. Mondel&#275;z International is a proud member of the Standard and Poor&#146;s 500, NASDAQ 100 and Dow Jones Sustainability Index. Visit
www.mondelezinternational.com or follow us on Twitter at <U>twitter.com/MDLZ</U>. </P> <P STYLE="line-height:8.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:10%">&nbsp;</P>

&#147;expect,&#148; &#147;would,&#148; &#147;intend,&#148; &#147;deliver,&#148; &#147;target,&#148; &#147;outlook&#148; and similar expressions are intended to identify our forward-looking statements, including, but not limited to, statements about:
our future performance, including our future revenue growth, operating income growth, earnings per share, margins and cash flow; focusing our portfolio; cost-reduction actions; productivity and productivity savings and improvement; supply chain and
overhead costs; our transformation agenda; investments; currency and the effect of foreign exchange translation on our results of operations; the costs of, timing of expenditures under and completion of our restructuring program; the cash proceeds
and ownership interest to be received in and timeframe for completing the coffee transactions; acquisitions; achievement of our strategic objectives; share repurchases; dividends; shareholder value; and our Outlook, including 2015 Organic Net
Revenue growth, Adjusted Operating Income margin, Adjusted EPS and Free Cash Flow. These forward-looking statements are subject to a number of risks and uncertainties, many of which are beyond our control, which could cause our actual results to
differ materially from those indicated in our forward-looking statements. Such factors include, but are not limited to, risks from operating globally and in emerging markets, changes in currency exchange rates, continued volatility of commodity and
other input costs, pricing actions, weakness in economic conditions, weakness in consumer spending, unanticipated disruptions to our business, competition, the restructuring program and our other transformation initiatives not yielding the
anticipated benefits, changes in the assumptions on which the restructuring program is based, failing to successfully complete the coffee transactions or other acquisitions on the anticipated time frames and tax law changes. Please also see our risk
factors, as they may be amended from time to time, set forth in our filings with the SEC, including our most recently filed Annual Report on Form 10-K. Mondel&#275;z International disclaims and does not undertake any obligation to update or revise
any forward-looking statement in this press release, except as required by applicable law or regulation. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. and Subsidiaries </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Reconciliation of GAAP and Non-GAAP Financial Measures </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>(Unaudited) </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The company reports its
financial results in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States (&#147;GAAP&#148; or referred to herein as &#147;Reported&#148;). However, management believes that certain non-GAAP financial measures should be
considered when assessing the company&#146;s ongoing performance to provide more complete information on the factors and trends affecting the company&#146;s business. Management also uses these non-GAAP financial measures in making financial,
operating and planning decisions and in evaluating the company&#146;s performance. Non-GAAP financial measures should be viewed in addition to, and not as an alternative for, the company&#146;s Reported results prepared in accordance with GAAP. In
addition, the non-GAAP measures the company uses may differ from non-GAAP measures used by other companies. Because GAAP financial measures on a forward-looking basis are neither accessible nor deemed to be significantly different from the non-GAAP
financial measures, and reconciling information is not available without unreasonable effort, the company has not provided that information with regard to the non-GAAP financial measures in the company&#146;s Outlook. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>DEFINITIONS OF THE COMPANY&#146;S NON-GAAP FINANCIAL MEASURES </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The company&#146;s non-GAAP financial measures and corresponding metrics reflect how the company evaluates its operating results currently and provide improved
comparability of operating results. As new events or circumstances arise, these definitions could change over time: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;Organic Net Revenue&#148; is defined as net revenues excluding the impact of acquisitions, divestitures (including businesses under sales agreements and exits of major product lines under a sale or licensing
agreement), Integration Program costs, accounting calendar changes and currency rate fluctuations. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;Adjusted Operating Income&#148; and &#147;Adjusted Segment Operating Income&#148; are defined as operating income (or segment operating income) excluding the impacts of Spin-Off Costs, pension costs related to the
obligations transferred in the Spin-Off, the 2012-2014 Restructuring Program, the 2014-2018 Restructuring Program, the Integration Program and other acquisition integration costs, the remeasurement of net monetary assets in Venezuela, the benefit
from the Cadbury acquisition-related indemnification resolution, incremental costs associated with the JDE coffee transactions, impairment charges related to goodwill and intangible assets, gains / losses from divestitures or acquisitions,
acquisition-related costs and the operating results of divestitures (including businesses under sales agreements and exits of major product lines under a sale or licensing agreement). The company also evaluates growth in the company&#146;s Adjusted
Operating Income and Adjusted Segment Operating Income on a constant currency basis. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">5 </P>

the Spin-Off, the 2012-2014 Restructuring Program, the 2014-2018 Restructuring Program, the Integration Program and other acquisition integration costs, the remeasurement of net monetary assets in Venezuela, the net benefit from the Cadbury
acquisition-related indemnification resolution, the loss on debt extinguishment and related expenses, the residual tax benefit impact from the resolution of the Starbucks arbitration, hedging gains / losses and incremental costs associated with the

</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">&#147;Free Cash Flow excluding items&#148; is defined as Free Cash Flow (net cash provided by operating activities less capital expenditures) excluding taxes paid on the Starbucks arbitration award and cash payments
associated with accrued interest and other related fees due to the company&#146;s completions of a $1.6 billion cash tender offer on February&nbsp;6, 2014 and a $3.4 billion cash tender offer on December&nbsp;18, 2013 for some of its outstanding
high coupon long-term debt. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">See the attached schedules for supplemental financial data and corresponding reconciliations of the non-GAAP
financial measures referenced in the Press Release to the most comparable GAAP financial measures. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>ITEMS IMPACTING COMPARABILITY OF OPERATING RESULTS
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The following information is provided to give qualitative and quantitative information related to items impacting comparability of operating results.
The company determines which items to consider as &#147;items impacting comparability&#148; based on how management views the company&#146;s business; makes financial, operating and planning decisions; and evaluates the company&#146;s ongoing
performance. In addition, the company provides the impact that changes in currency exchange rates had on the company&#146;s financial results (referred to as &#147;constant currency&#148;). </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">6 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Divestitures </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The company excludes the operating results of businesses divested, including businesses under sales agreements and exits of major product lines under a sale or
licensing agreement. The company did not divest any businesses during the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. In 2013, the company completed several divestitures primarily in the company&#146;s EEMEA and Europe segments. These divestitures
included a salty snacks business in Turkey, a confectionery business in South Africa and a chocolate business in Spain. In addition, the company exited a major product line under a licensing agreement in the company&#146;s North America segment. In
connection with the divestitures in Turkey and South Africa, the company recognized a pre-tax gain of $8 million during the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2013. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Acquisition </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On February&nbsp;22, 2013, the
company acquired the remaining interest in a biscuit operation in Morocco, which is now a wholly-owned subsidiary within the company&#146;s EEMEA segment. The company recorded a pre-tax gain of $22 million during the three months ended
March&nbsp;31, 2013 related to the remeasurement of the company&#146;s previously-held equity interest in the operation to fair value in accordance with GAAP. For 2014, only the operating results for the period prior to the anniversary date of the
acquisition are noted as an item impacting comparability. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Integration Program and other acquisition integration costs </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Integration Program costs </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Integration Program costs are
defined as the costs associated with combining the Mondel&#275;z International and Cadbury businesses, and are separate from those costs associated with completing the acquisition. At the end of 2013, the company completed incurring charges related
to the Integration Program. The company recorded reversals to the Integration Program of $8 million in the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 related to accruals no longer required. The company recorded charges of $216 million during the
twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2013 in selling, general and administrative expenses within its Europe, Asia Pacific, Latin America and EEMEA segments. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Other acquisition integration costs </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In connection with
the acquisition of a biscuit operation in Morocco in February 2013, the company recorded integration charges of $4 million for the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 and $4 million for the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2013. The
company recorded these charges in selling, general and administrative expenses within the company&#146;s EEMEA segment. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">7 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Spin-Off Costs </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On October&nbsp;1, 2012, the company completed the Spin-Off of its North American grocery business, Kraft Foods Group, Inc. (&#147;Kraft Foods Group&#148;), to
its shareholders (the &#147;Spin-Off&#148;). Following the Spin-Off, Kraft Foods Group is an independent public company and the company does not beneficially own any shares of Kraft Foods Group common stock. In 2014, the company concluded its
Spin-Off transition plans. Historically the company has incurred Spin-Off transaction, transition and financing and related costs (&#147;Spin-Off Costs&#148;) in its operating results. Within selling, general and administrative expenses, the company
recorded $35 million of pre-tax Spin-Off Costs in the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 and $62 million in the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2013. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>2012-2014 Restructuring Program </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In 2012, the
company&#146;s Board of Directors approved $1.5 billion of restructuring and related implementation costs (&#147;2012-2014 Restructuring Program&#148;) reflecting primarily severance, asset disposals and other manufacturing-related one-time costs.
The primary objective of the restructuring and implementation activities was to ensure that both Mondel&#275;z International and Kraft Foods Group were each set up to operate efficiently and execute on their respective business strategies upon
separation and in the future. Of the $1.5 billion of anticipated 2012-2014 Restructuring Program costs, the company retained approximately $925 million and Kraft Foods Group retained the balance of the program. Through the end of 2014, the company
has incurred total restructuring and implementation costs of $899 million and does not expect to incur additional charges on the 2012-2014 Restructuring Program. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Restructuring costs </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The company recorded within asset
impairment and exit costs charges of $360 million in the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 as compared to $267 million in the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2013. These charges were related to asset write-downs (including accelerated
depreciation and asset impairments), severance and other related costs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Implementation costs </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Implementation costs are directly attributable to restructuring activities; however, they do not qualify for accounting treatment as exit or disposal
activities. The company recorded implementation costs of $99 million in the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 as compared to $63 million in the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2013. Implementation costs primarily include costs to
reorganize the company&#146;s operations and facilities, the discontinuance of certain product lines and the incremental expenses related to the closure of facilities, replicating the company&#146;s information systems infrastructure and
reorganizing costs related to the company&#146;s sales function. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">8 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Acquisition-related costs </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On November&nbsp;11, 2014, the Company announced the pending acquisition of a biscuit operation in Vietnam. The biscuit operation will become a wholly-owned
subsidiary within the company&#146;s Asia Pacific segment. The company expects to close the transaction in mid-2015 after regulatory and other matters are resolved. The company recorded $2 million in acquisition-related costs during the three months
ended December&nbsp;31, 2014, which was recorded in selling, general and administrative expenses. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">In connection, with the acquisition of the biscuit
operation in Morocco in February 2013, the company recorded a total of $7 million in acquisition-related costs during the three months ended March&nbsp;31, 2013, of which $5 million was recorded in interest and other expense, net and $2 million in
selling, general and administrative expenses. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Net benefit from Indemnification Resolution </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As part of the 2010 Cadbury acquisition, the company became the responsible party for tax matters under the Cadbury Schweppes Plc and Dr Pepper Snapple Group,
Inc. (&#147;DPSG&#148;) Tax Sharing and Indemnification Agreement dated May&nbsp;1, 2008 (&#147;Tax Indemnity&#148;) for certain 2007 and 2008 transactions relating to the demerger of Cadbury&#146;s Americas Beverage business. A U.S. federal tax
audit of DPSG for the 2006-2008 tax years was concluded with the IRS in August 2013. As a result, the company recorded a favorable impact of $336 million in selling, general and administrative expenses and $49 million in interest and other expense,
net for a total pre-tax impact of $385 million ($363 million net of tax) in the three months ended September&nbsp;30, 2013 due to the reversal of the accrued liability in excess of the amount paid to DPSG under the Tax Indemnity in the third quarter
of 2013. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Remeasurement of Venezuelan net monetary assets </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As a result of recent Venezuelan currency exchange developments and the expected impact on the company&#146;s Venezuelan operations, the company remeasured its
Venezuelan bolivar-denominated net monetary assets as of March&nbsp;31, 2014 from the official exchange rate of 6.30 to the then-prevailing SICAD I exchange rate of 10.70 bolivars to the U.S. dollar. The company recognized a $142 million currency
remeasurement pre-tax charge within selling, general&nbsp;&amp; administrative expenses. Through December 2014, the company recognized $25 million of additional remeasurement charges in operating income related primarily to changes in the SICAD I
rate. While the remeasurement loss is non-deductible, a $16 million net tax benefit for 2014 was recognized due to a Venezuelan tax impact related to a local deduction for the loss on certain U.S. dollar denominated liabilities partially offset by
the tax impact due to interest deductibility limitations resulting from Venezuela&#146;s lower earnings. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">9 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">As of December&nbsp;31, 2014, the company&#146;s remaining bolivar-denominated net monetary assets were
approximately $236 million. The company&#146;s Venezuela net revenues were approximately $760 million or 2.2% of consolidated net revenues for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">During the three months ended March&nbsp;31, 2013, the company also recorded a $54 million currency remeasurement pre-tax charge related to the devaluation of
the company&#146;s net monetary assets in Venezuela at that time. In addition, due to the company&#146;s underlying legal structure, higher taxes of $5 million were recorded due primarily to interest deductibility limitations resulting from
Venezuela&#146;s lower earnings. As described in the company&#146;s Form 8-K dated April&nbsp;22, 2014, this 2013 remeasurement charge was previously included in the company&#146;s non-GAAP financial measures of Adjusted Operating Income and
Adjusted Earnings Per Share. This charge is now excluded from these non-GAAP financial measures. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The company continues to monitor developments in the
currency and actively manage its investment and exposures in Venezuela. If any of the rates, or application of the rates to the company&#146;s business, were to change, the company would recognize additional currency losses or gains, which could be
significant. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>2014-2018 Restructuring Program </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On May&nbsp;6, 2014, the company&#146;s Board of Directors approved a $3.5 billion restructuring program, comprised of approximately $2.5 billion in cash costs
and $1 billion in non-cash costs (&#147;2014-2018 Restructuring Program&#148;), and up to $2.2 billion of capital expenditures. The primary objective of the 2014-2018 Restructuring Program is to reduce the company&#146;s operating cost structure in
both supply chain and overhead costs. The program is intended primarily to cover severance as well as asset disposals and other manufacturing-related one-time costs.The company expects to incur the majority of the program&#146;s charges in 2015 and
2016 and to complete the program by year-end 2018. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Restructuring costs </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The company recorded within asset impairment and exit costs charges of $274 million in the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. These charges were for
asset write-downs (including accelerated depreciation and asset impairments), severance and other related costs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Implementation costs </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Implementation costs are directly attributable to restructuring activities; however, they do not qualify for special accounting treatment as exit or disposal
activities. The company recorded implementation costs of $107 million in the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">10 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">These costs primarily relate to reorganizing the company&#146;s operations and facilities in connection with its
supply chain reinvention program and other identified productivity and cost saving initiatives. The costs include incremental expenses related to the closure of facilities, costs to terminate certain contracts and the simplification of the
company&#146;s information systems. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Unrealized hedging gains / losses and incremental costs for the JDE coffee transactions </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On May&nbsp;7, 2014, the company announced that it entered into an agreement to combine the company&#146;s wholly owned coffee portfolio (outside of France)
with D.E Master Blenders 1753 B.V. In conjunction with this transaction, Acorn Holdings B.V. (&#147;AHBV&#148;), owner of D.E Master Blenders 1753, has made a binding offer to receive the company&#146;s coffee business in France. The parties have
also invited the company&#146;s partners in certain joint ventures to join the new company. The transactions remain subject to regulatory approvals and the completion of employee information and consultation requirements. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Upon completion of all proposed transactions, the company will receive cash of approximately &#128;4 billion and a 49 percent equity interest in the new
company, to be called Jacobs Douwe Egberts. AHBV will hold a majority share in the proposed combined company and will have a majority of the seats on the board, which will be chaired by current D.E Master Blenders 1753 Chairman Bart Becht. AHBV is
owned by an investor group led by JAB Holding Company s.&agrave; r.l. The company will have certain minority rights. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Certain expenses related to readying
the businesses for the planned transactions have been incurred. Within selling, general and administrative expenses, incremental costs were $77 million in the twelve months ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 and were incurred primarily in the
company&#146;s Europe and EEMEA segments and general corporate expense. Within interest and other expense, net, the company also recorded unrealized gains of $215 million in the three months and $628 million in the twelve months ended
December&nbsp;31, 2014 in connection with currency exchange forward contracts entered into to hedge the expected cash receipt of &#128;4 billion upon closing. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Intangible Asset Impairment </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">During the 2014
review of non-amortizable intangible assets, the company recorded $57 million of impairment charges related to two trademarks in the three months ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. In both cases, the impairments arose due to lower than expected product
growth and decisions to redirect support for the products to other regional brands. The charges relate to a biscuit trademark in the company&#146;s Asia Pacific segment and a candy trademark in the company&#146;s Europe segment. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">11 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>Constant currency </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Management evaluates the operating performance of the company and its international subsidiaries on a constant currency basis. The company determines its
constant currency operating results by dividing or multiplying, as appropriate, the current period local currency operating results by the currency exchange rates used to translate the company&#146;s financial statements in the comparable prior year
period to determine what the current period U.S. dollar operating results would have been if the currency exchange rate had not changed from the comparable prior year period. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">12 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></TD>

<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom"><B>%&nbsp;</B></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1px; ">

<div style='position:absolute;left:158px;top:483px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:8px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>current rather than average 2013 currency rates for the hyperinflationary markets of Venezuela and

4.3% for the Total Portfolio.</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:627px;top:485px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:"times new roman","times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'> </div>

<div style='position:absolute;left:54px;top:218px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#00B7C6;'>&#150;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:72px;top:218px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>Key driver +300bps&nbsp; OI margin in Europe</div>

<td nowrap> <div style='position:absolute;left:10px;top:78px'>
<img src="g873683ex99_2s61gbgd.jpg" width="900" height="450" border="0"alt=" "></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:71px;top:5px;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;font-size:24px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#4F2170;'>DEFINITIONS OF THE COMPANY&#146;S NON&#45;GAAP FINANCIAL MEASURES</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:36px;top:44px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>The company&#146;s non&#45;GAAP financial measures and corresponding metrics reflect how the company
evaluates its operating results currently and provide improved </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:36px;top:57px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>comparability of operating
results.&nbsp; As new events or circumstances arise, these definitions could change over time: </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:87px;top:75px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;Organic Net Revenue&#148; is defined as net revenues excluding the impact of acquisitions,
divestitures (including businesses under sales agreements and </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:87px;top:89px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>exits of major product lines under
a sale or licensing agreement), Integration Program costs, accounting calendar changes and currency rate fluctuations.</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:87px;top:105px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:3px;font-family:"times new roman","times new roman",times,serif;color:#CE1126;'> </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:86px;top:106px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;Adjusted Gross Profit&#148; is defined as gross profit excluding the impacts of pension costs
related to obligations transferred in the Spin&#45;Off, the 2012&#45;2014 </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:86px;top:120px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Restructuring
Program, the Integration Program and other acquisition integration costs and the operating results of divestitures (including businesses </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:86px;top:133px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>under sales agreements and exits of major product lines under a sale or licensing agreement).&nbsp;
The company also evaluates growth in the company&#146;s </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:86px;top:147px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Adjusted Gross Profit on a constant
currency basis. </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:86px;top:161px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:4px;font-family:"times new roman","times new roman",times,serif;color:#CE1126;'> </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:165px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;Adjusted Operating Income&#148; and &#147;Adjusted Segment Operating Income&#148; are defined as
operating income (or segment operating income) excluding the </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:179px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>impacts of Spin&#45;Off Costs,
pension costs related to the obligations transferred in the Spin&#45;Off, the 2012&#45;2014 Restructuring Program, the 2014&#45;2018 </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:193px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Restructuring Program, the Integration Program and other acquisition integration costs, the
remeasurement of net monetary assets in Venezuela, the </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:206px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>benefit from the Cadbury
acquisition&#45;related indemnification resolution, incremental costs associated with the JDE coffee transactions, impairment </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:220px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>charges related to goodwill and intangible assets, gains / losses from divestitures or acquisitions,
acquisition&#45;related costs and the operating results of </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:234px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>divestitures (including businesses
under sales agreements and exits of major product lines under a sale or licensing agreement).&nbsp; The company also </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:248px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>evaluates growth in the company&#146;s Adjusted Operating Income and Adjusted Segment Operating Income
on a constant currency basis. </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:262px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:4px;font-family:"times new roman","times new roman",times,serif;color:#CE1126;'> </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:266px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;Adjusted EPS&#148;&nbsp; is defined as diluted EPS attributable to Mondelez International from
continuing operations excluding the impacts of Spin&#45;Off Costs, </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:279px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>pension costs related to the
obligations transferred in the Spin&#45;Off, the 2012&#45;2014 Restructuring Program, the 2014&#45;2018 Restructuring Program, the </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:293px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Integration Program and other acquisition integration costs, the remeasurement of net monetary assets
in Venezuela, the net benefit from the Cadbury </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:307px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>acquisition&#45;related indemnification
resolution, the loss on debt extinguishment and related expenses, the residual tax benefit impact from the resolution </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:321px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>of the Starbucks arbitration, hedging gains / losses and incremental costs associated with the JDE
coffee transactions, impairment charges related to </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:334px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>goodwill and intangible assets, gains /
losses from divestitures or acquisitions, acquisition&#45;related costs and net earnings from divestitures (including </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:348px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>businesses under sales agreements and exits of major product lines under a sale or licensing
agreement), and including an interest expense adjustment</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:361px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>related to the Spin&#45;Off&nbsp;
transaction.&nbsp; The company also evaluates growth in the company&#146;s Adjusted EPS on a constant currency basis.&nbsp; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:376px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:4px;font-family:"times new roman","times new roman",times,serif;color:#CE1126;'> </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:380px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;Free Cash Flow excluding items&#148; is defined as Free Cash Flow (net cash provided by
operating activities less capital expenditures) excluding taxes paid</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:394px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>on the Starbucks
arbitration award and cash payments associated with accrued interest and other related fees due to the company&#146;s completion of a </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:407px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>$1.6 billion cash tender offer&nbsp; on February 6, 2014 and a $3.4 billion cash tender offer on
December 18, 2013 for some of its outstanding high&#45;coupon </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:90px;top:421px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>long&#45;term debt. <font
face='"times new roman","times new roman",times,serif' color='#CE1126'> </font></div> </td></tr></table></div>

<div style='position:absolute;left:229px;top:179px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>Divestitures</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:600px;top:179px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>&#45;</div>

<div style='position:absolute;left:588px;top:194px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>(14)</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:229px;top:208px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>Currency</div>
